First one I ever posted was back in August. I’d say it’s been a mix of having a fair amount of downtime at work to brainstorm ideas, as well as being able to use ideas I was sitting on for a long time. I originally wanted to do some of my stories (like BFG) in regular longform prose, but greentext has been so much easier to get ideas out without stressing about length or formatting. So I get to use concepts that would otherwise have probably stayed in creative limbo forever.

And sometimes inspiration just hits, like when I picked up the anon’s prompt for Stacked Up. The ideas just kind of snowballed after reading the idea for it.

I’ve always seen greentext stories as similar to dialogue boxes in video games or text adventures. Brief snippets of the action, narrowed down to what’s most important in a scene at the very moment it happens, rather than recounting past events. -Coughing Fit

I find as i'm rounding out this introductory chapter that the greentext formatting, although my paragraph separation probably fits nowhere in the 2k character limit for posting, is great for looking at each sentence or action in the chain individually and picking out problems or repetition.
